@startuml seq_debate_flow
title "Whose Side Are You On?" — Debate Mode Sequence

actor       "Host"          as Host
participant "Host UI\n(host.js)" as HostUI
participant "Backend\n(FastAPI)" as Backend
participant "Training Daemon\n(training_daemon.py)" as Daemon
participant "Claude API\n(Anthropic)" as Claude
participant "Participant UI\n(participant.js)" as PaxUI
actor       "Participant"   as Pax

== Launch Debate ==

Host -> HostUI : Type statement\n+ click "Launch Debate"
HostUI -> Backend : POST /api/debate\n{statement: "Microservices > Monolith"}
Backend -> Backend : store statement\nset phase = side_selection
Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: state\n{debate, phase=side_selection}
Backend --> PaxUI : WS broadcast: state\n{debate, phase=side_selection}
PaxUI -> Pax : show FOR / AGAINST buttons\n(blind choice — no arguments yet)

== Phase 1 — Side Selection ==

Pax -> PaxUI : click FOR or AGAINST
PaxUI -> Backend : WS: {type: debate_pick_side,\nside: "for"|"against"}
Backend -> Backend : record side choice\n(all participants can pick freely)
Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: side counts update
Backend --> PaxUI : WS: confirmation\n"You chose FOR ✓"

Host -> HostUI : Click "Close Selection"
HostUI -> Backend : POST /api/debate/close-selection
Backend -> Backend : auto-assign remaining\nparticipants to balance sides
Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: state\n{phase=arguments, all sides assigned}
Backend --> PaxUI : WS broadcast: state\n{your_side, phase=arguments}
PaxUI -> Pax : show assigned side\n(may differ from preference\nfor late joiners)

== Phase 2 — Arguments ==

HostUI -> Host : show dual-column layout\n(LEFT=AGAINST, RIGHT=FOR)
PaxUI -> Pax : show dual-column +\ntext input for own side

Pax -> PaxUI : type argument + submit
PaxUI -> Backend : WS: {type: debate_argument,\ntext: "Easier to scale independently"}
Backend -> Backend : store argument\n(author, side, timestamp)\naward points to author
Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: new argument\n(appears in correct column)
Backend --> PaxUI : WS broadcast: new argument\n(all participants see it)

Pax -> PaxUI : click existing argument\nto upvote
PaxUI -> Backend : WS: {type: debate_upvote,\nargument_id: "arg_123"}
Backend -> Backend : record upvote\n+25 pts upvoter\n+50 pts author
Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: upvote count update
Backend --> PaxUI : WS broadcast: upvote count update

Host -> HostUI : Click "End Arguments"
HostUI -> Backend : POST /api/debate/end-arguments
Backend -> Backend : queue AI cleanup request\nin state

== Phase 3 — AI Cleanup & Augmentation ==

Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: state\n{phase=ai_cleanup}
Backend --> PaxUI : WS broadcast: state\n{phase=ai_cleanup, read-only}
HostUI -> Host : show arguments read-only\n+ "Waiting for AI..." indicator

Daemon -> Backend : GET /api/debate/ai-request\n(poll loop)
Backend --> Daemon : {arguments, statement}
Daemon -> Claude : Send all arguments\n+ statement for cleanup
Claude --> Daemon : deduplicated + cleaned args\n+ new suggestions
Daemon -> Backend : POST /api/debate/ai-result\n{cleaned arguments + AI additions}
Backend -> Backend : update existing args\n(fix typos, deduplicate)\nadd AI args marked with ✨
Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: state\n{updated arguments}
Backend --> PaxUI : WS broadcast: state\n{updated arguments}
HostUI -> Host : show cleaned arguments\n+ ✨ AI additions in both columns
PaxUI -> Pax : show cleaned arguments\n+ ✨ AI additions (read-only)

Host -> HostUI : Click "Next Phase"
HostUI -> Backend : POST /api/debate/phase\n{phase: "prep"}

== Phase 4 — Preparation ==

note over HostUI, PaxUI
  Host chooses: breakout rooms (external tool)
  OR in-app thinking pause with hints
end note

Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: state\n{phase=prep}
Backend --> PaxUI : WS broadcast: state\n{phase=prep}
HostUI -> Host : show all arguments\n+ debate rules\n+ attack/defense hints
PaxUI -> Pax : show own side's arguments\n+ debate rules + hints\n+ "Volunteer as Champion" button

Pax -> PaxUI : click "Volunteer as Champion"
PaxUI -> Backend : WS: {type: debate_volunteer}
Backend -> Backend : first-come wins\naward 2500 pts
Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast:\nchampion assigned {side, name}
Backend --> PaxUI : WS broadcast:\nchampion assigned
PaxUI -> Pax : "🏆 You are your team's champion!"\nor "Champion: [Name]"

Host -> HostUI : Click "Start Debate"
HostUI -> Backend : POST /api/debate/phase\n{phase: "live_debate"}

== Phase 5 — Live Debate ==

Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: state\n{phase=live_debate}
Backend --> PaxUI : WS broadcast: state\n{phase=live_debate}
HostUI -> Host : show champions' names\n+ arguments summary\n+ debate rules on screen

note over Host, Pax
  Champions debate live (voice/video).
  Host picks which side speaks first,
  starts a timer per round, and can end rounds early.
  Rules and hints remain visible on screen.
end note

Host -> HostUI : Pick first side to speak
HostUI -> Backend : POST /api/debate/first-side\n{side: "for"|"against"}
Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: state\n{first_side}
Backend --> PaxUI : WS broadcast: state\n{first_side}

Host -> HostUI : Click "Start Round Timer"
HostUI -> Backend : POST /api/debate/round-timer
Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: state\n{round timer started}
Backend --> PaxUI : WS broadcast: state\n{round timer started}

Host -> HostUI : Click "End Round" (optional, early)
HostUI -> Backend : POST /api/debate/end-round
Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: state\n{round ended}
Backend --> PaxUI : WS broadcast: state\n{round ended}

PaxUI -> Pax : show champions' names\n+ key arguments\n+ debate hints

Host -> HostUI : Click "End Debate"
HostUI -> Backend : POST /api/debate/phase\n{phase: "ended"}
Backend -> Backend : finalize scores
Backend --> HostUI : WS broadcast: state\n{phase=ended, final scores}
Backend --> PaxUI : WS broadcast: state\n{phase=ended, final scores}

@enduml
